                <note rend="inline" type="source">511.4 A 2a/23: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Consul at Geneva</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Band</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Geneva</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-12-15T11:00:00+01:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">December 15, 1928—11 a.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/>[Received December 15—10:15 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>The Council of the League has appointed May<note n="83" xml:id="d318fn83">Herbert
                        L. May, of Pittsburgh.</note> (American) a member of the Central Board
                    provided for by the Geneva Opium Convention of 1925. Full report by mail.<note
                        n="81" xml:id="d318fn81">Not printed.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Rand</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
